## Flutter
 - Flutter is Google's portable UI toolkit for crafting beautiful, natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop from a single codebase. 
 - Flutter works with existing code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is free and open source.
 
 ## Steps of flutter Installation
 1). Install zip file flutter software(around 829 mb) 
       - For Windows: https://storage.googleapis.com/flutter_infra_release/releases/stable/windows/flutter_windows_2.2.1-stable.zip
       - Warning: Do not install Flutter in a directory like C:\Program Files\ that requires elevated privileges.
       
 2). Extract the zip file and set path in Environemnt Variables.
 
 3). Use 'flutter --version' & 'dart --version' command to check it's properly set or not.
 
 4). Install Android Studio Software to get SDK for the Android required for the flutter.
       - For Windows: https://developer.android.com/studio
       
 5). Copy path of Android Studio Software.
 
 6). Open Android Studio Software after installation & click on 'Configure' & then go inside 'SDK Manager', then Copy the path of Android SDK.
 
 7). Open Window CMD and run these commands:
       - flutter config --android-sdk="<paste android sdk path>"
       - flutter config --android-studio-dir="<paste android studio software path>"
       
  8). Recommended IDE for flutter to write the code in dart langusge is VsCode, so install it set path in environment variables. Inside VsCode install 'flutter' and 'dart'
      extensions to get more features of flutter.
        - Installation Link: https://code.visualstudio.com/download
  
  9). Finally to check everything is fit & fine, open window cmd & run:
        - flutter doctor --android-licenses    ( used to download the required licenses for flutter)
        - flutter doctor
